Dialogue: 5,0:03:20.85,0:03:23.09,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,Most pros use the G-pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:23.09,0:03:26.45,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,The control G-pens give over the intensity of the line really increases quality.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:28.10,0:03:30.27,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,I never got used to it, so I use a Kabura pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:31.09,0:03:33.15,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,This type of pen just makes the cut for the purposes of gag manga,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:33.15,0:03:35.03,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,But real pros should use G-pens.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:35.98,0:03:39.47,Default,Uncle,0000,0000,0000,,I try to use one sometimes, but it's really difficult.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:56.00,0:03:57.17,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:57.51,0:03:59.65,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Mashiro, wake up!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:00.05,0:04:00.84,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:00.84,0:04:01.84,Q_Q,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh crap!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:02.72,0:04:07.71,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,It's great that you're studying hard, but your effort's wasted if you fall asleep in the middle of the test.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:07.71,0:04:09.67,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:11.55,0:04:13.66,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Finally done for the day.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:15.28,0:04:16.75,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You alright?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:16.75,0:04:19.98,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen someone pass out in the middle of a test before.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:21.13,0:04:22.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Saiko!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:22.32,0:04:25.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really pass out from studying too hard?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:25.52,0:04:26.78,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:26.78,0:04:30.13,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever, it's over and done with. Wanna hit the movies?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:30.13,0:04:32.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Let's see something x-rated!
Dialogue: 5,0:04:32.26,0:04:33.62,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,X-rated?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.62,0:04:36.28,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I've got stuff to do.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:37.20,0:04:38.04,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with them?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:38.04,0:04:41.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Those two have been inseparable lately.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:42.84,0:04:45.85,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Were you up all night practicing drawing?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:45.85,0:04:47.72,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was at the studio past midnight.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:47.72,0:04:51.41,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Then I went home and practiced till it was time for school.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:51.41,0:04:55.71,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,If I didn't lose my drawing streak on the way to school, I might've taken the test with this pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:56.44,0:04:59.02,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... you even brought it with you and everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:59.02,0:05:02.15,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't get used to using this, it's over.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:02.15,0:05:04.05,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any boundaries in manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.05,0:05:04.90,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Boundaries?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.90,0:05:07.91,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike tests, there isn't one way to do manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:08.32,0:05:10.36,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Stories and pictures don't have right or wrong answers.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:13.11,0:05:15.55,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna head over to the studio now, you wanna come along?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:15.55,0:05:16.65,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:16.65,0:05:18.30,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You seem pumped.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:20.84,0:05:23.35,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go. Your own key to the studio.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:25.09,0:05:26.78,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You sure?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.20,0:05:29.58,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's better if you can get in whenever you need to, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:30.99,0:05:32.07,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wow, thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:32.86,0:05:36.09,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Since exams are finally over, we can really get down to it.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:40.30,0:05:41.36,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:41.65,0:05:44.50,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You're seriously talented, Saiko.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:44.75,0:05:47.11,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You can produce this caliber of drawing in just one day!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:47.11,0:05:48.87,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Those are no good at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:48.87,0:05:49.96,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with them?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:49.96,0:05:53.16,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The lines are too stiff; the thickness and stress points are a mess.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:53.16,0:05:55.30,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,They couldn't pass as manga works.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:55.30,0:05:56.65,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:57.36,0:05:59.27,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's really is hard to get used to the G-pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:59.78,0:06:02.63,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't get the lines to form the way I picture them.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.93,0:06:05.76,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I even tried using the Kabura pen once instead.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:06.45,0:06:07.84,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,A Kabura pen?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:07.84,0:06:08.63,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,This one.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:08.63,0:06:12.15,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. I thought fountain pens \Nreferred to that one in general.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:12.15,0:06:15.76,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly my uncle didn't know about G-pens either. So he drew with a Kabura pen instead.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:15.76,0:06:16.90,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:16.90,0:06:19.98,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Then his editor told him to use a G-pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.81,0:06:23.89,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But he was used to the Kabura pen and couldn't get a hang of the G-pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:23.89,0:06:26.15,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,So he ended up only using the Kabura pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.11,0:06:30.24,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have much control over the thickness of lines,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:30.24,0:06:33.03,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But with a Kabura pen, it's much \Neasier to produce a consistent line.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:34.91,0:06:37.85,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,With a G-pen, on the other hand, you have \Nmuch more control over the intensity of lines.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:40.37,0:06:42.21,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But its inflexibility makes it \Nprone to get stuck on the paper.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:42.21,0:06:44.02,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:44.02,0:06:48.55,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,So the Kabura pen is no good, even \Nthough your uncle used one as a pro?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:48.55,0:06:50.56,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it's no good!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:50.56,0:06:52.60,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,My pictures would have no dimension if I used it.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:52.95,0:06:55.80,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle always insisted that his drawings were terrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:55.80,0:06:58.52,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He said they just barely made the cut because it was gag manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:58.52,0:06:59.99,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he had a point...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:00.55,0:07:05.73,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's completely different from making sketches in pencil, to fill in with paint afterward.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:06.22,0:07:08.20,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The only way is to practice till it hurts.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:09.75,0:07:11.67,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Here's some more of the stuff I worked on last night.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:14.45,0:07:15.63,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:15.63,0:07:17.54,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Or I guess I shouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:17.54,0:07:20.06,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,He's not satisfied with this at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:20.80,0:07:23.73,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You can draw better backgrounds with a Kabura pen.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:25.84,0:07:27.97,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,And a Maru pen can be used for the extremely thin lines.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:31.00,0:07:32.57,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you use those for a model?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:32.57,0:07:36.43,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I took out all of stuff that was packed in those boxes.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:37.80,0:07:39.31,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know they sold this sort of material...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:39.90,0:07:42.07,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You can make a great manuscript using this, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.48,0:07:43.77,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Not without adding impact.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:44.06,0:07:44.92,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Impact?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:46.43,0:07:47.26,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,These.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:48.06,0:07:51.53,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly my uncle assigned these to his assistant using the numbers,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:51.78,0:07:53.41,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But we have to do it ourselves first.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:53.41,0:07:56.23,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna draw all of these by hand?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:56.23,0:07:58.31,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Using these tools, yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:59.65,0:08:01.91,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we have an assistant,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:01.91,0:08:04.53,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,So we even have to apply the screen tones ourselves too.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:05.35,0:08:08.09,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You cut these out with an art knife then apply them.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:09.98,0:08:12.99,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, to make just one page of a manuscript, we'd need to...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:13.60,0:08:17.92,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,First, we make a rough sketch on draft paper based on the name.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:17.92,0:08:20.39,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Then add in the characters and the background using a pen?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:20.39,0:08:25.66,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Then we'd paint in the black, impact areas using a screen tone.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:25.66,0:08:27.90,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,All that to finish just one page?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:28.70,0:08:30.82,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,That's so much...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:30.82,0:08:31.69,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:32.25,0:08:36.82,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,That workflow process depends on the person, but that's basically it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:38.57,0:08:45.67,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I've finally realized just how much we have to master before we can produce something worth submitting.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:46.21,0:08:48.86,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to draw a person standing still,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:49.56,0:08:53.00,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But unless I can capture movement, expressions, and create composition,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:53.00,0:08:55.45,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never become a pro.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:55.45,0:08:57.46,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,That'll take an incredible amount of time.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:58.95,0:09:04.64,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking back on it now, it's amazing my uncle began as a complete amateur and debuted in just three years.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:04.96,0:09:07.58,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't know about whiteout.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:07.58,0:09:11.57,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,So if he made even the slightest \Nmistake, he'd redraw the entire thing.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:11.57,0:09:13.64,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is that right?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:13.64,0:09:15.20,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't a choice!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.20,0:09:17.43,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,If we want an anime by the time we're eighteen,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:17.43,0:09:19.91,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have a second to waste!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:20.62,0:09:24.01,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Saiko, I understand where you're coming from.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:24.01,0:09:27.66,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,But you should spend a little time studying the day before an exam.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.66,0:09:29.19,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:29.19,0:09:31.90,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I meant to study a little yesterday...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.90,0:09:34.00,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But it was morning before I knew it.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.00,0:09:35.49,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Before you knew it...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:35.78,0:09:38.38,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, we've got to start putting in effort now.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:38.38,0:09:42.31,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,According to my uncle, that's one of the conditions for becoming a manga artist.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.31,0:09:44.46,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Conditions for becoming a manga artist?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:44.46,0:09:46.57,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,In the Taro Kawaguchi school of thought.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:46.57,0:09:49.23,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The three great conditions for becoming a manga artist, if you're not a genius.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:50.90,0:09:52.61,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,T-Teach me!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.99,0:09:54.23,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:10:07.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H2A3033&\fnBrianne's hand\pos(195,55)}{\fs35}Number One
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:10:07.04,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H2A3033&\fnBrianne's hand\pos(195,94)}{\fs65}Pride
Dialogue: 5,0:09:55.51,0:09:56.80,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Pride!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:56.80,0:09:59.85,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Think that you're way better than everyone else.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:59.85,0:10:01.48,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, I've got that one down already.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.48,0:10:04.64,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, it's not just pride. It's the truth.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:04.64,0:10:07.05,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,That would be called pride.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:07.05,0:10:08.37,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.37,0:10:13.84,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H2A3033&\fnBrianne's hand\pos(195,55)}{\fs35}Number Two
Dialogue: 5,0:10:09.30,0:10:10.05,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Effort!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.37,0:10:13.84,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H2A3033&\fnBrianne's hand\pos(195,94)}{\fs65}Effort
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.85,0:10:13.84,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this time it's something \Nupstanding, Mr. Taro Kawaguchi.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.84,0:10:15.46,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,And lastly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:20.76,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\c&H2A3033&\fnBrianne's hand\pos(171,92)}{\fs35}Number Three\N{\fs70}Luck
Dialogue: 5,0:10:17.20,0:10:18.49,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, luck.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:18.86,0:10:19.55,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:20.76,0:10:23.64,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You serious? Luck?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:23.64,0:10:25.27,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:25.27,0:10:28.06,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,We're gamblers, not geniuses after all.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:28.57,0:10:31.36,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Just sitting around talking about our \Ndreams won't make them come true.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:31.61,0:10:34.31,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna spend the entire weekend drawing.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:37.54,0:10:38.65,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:38.65,0:10:41.53,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm gonna read all of the manga in this studio!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:49.82,0:10:52.62,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,This "Father's Soul" story really gets to you...
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.52,0:11:06.40,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,"My friends stood behind us in a row, as if to watch till we were out of sight."
Dialogue: 5,0:11:06.40,0:11:08.07,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.56,0:11:12.10,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\b1\bord0\c&H82847D&\fnGaramond\frz348.674\move(414,313,550,315,0,3527)}Modern\NJapanese
Dialogue: 5,0:11:09.01,0:11:11.59,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Right, then next... Suzuki!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:11.59,0:11:12.74,Default,Suzuki,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes sir!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.74,0:11:14.06,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, wait, never mind.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:14.06,0:11:15.57,Default,Suzuki,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:15.57,0:11:17.60,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,No reason in particular.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:17.60,0:11:18.77,Default,Suzuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's mean!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:18.77,0:11:20.03,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Kawasaki, you read please.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:22.15,0:11:23.79,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to the studio after this, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:24.07,0:11:24.86,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.20,0:11:26.70,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get this week's Jack.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:26.70,0:11:28.31,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:28.31,0:11:29.91,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Who's on the cover for this week...?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.75,0:11:33.19,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Do I need anything else?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:33.19,0:11:33.99,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Saiko!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.42,0:11:36.11,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Come here, come here!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:37.79,0:11:38.68,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:38.68,0:11:41.93,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the winner of the Tezuka Award's been announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.92,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(583,76)\frz339.274}Winner Announced!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.92,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\frx20\fry0\frz348.498\pos(286,150)}Prize
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.92,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(486,221)\frz339.503}1mil yen
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.92,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord3\frz340.587\3c&H404B47&\pos(361,225)}Winner
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.92,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord2\c&H3D4743&\frz342.61\pos(322,350)\3c&HA5C2BB&}Eiji Nizuma (15) Aomori
Dialogue: 5,0:11:42.20,0:11:44.01,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,The winner is...!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:44.01,0:11:45.08,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:45.08,0:11:47.15,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,His age! Look at how old he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:49.64,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs40\bord2\c&H3D4743&\3c&HA5C2BB&\move(240,20,240,148,0,1735)}Eiji Nizuma (15) Aomori
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:11:58.61,Tezuka Award,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)\q2\an7\fs80\bord2\c&H3D4743&\3c&HA5C2BB&\move(98,357,-320,357,0,3112)}Eiji Nizuma (15) Aomori
Dialogue: 5,0:11:58.60,0:11:59.74,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He's only fifteen...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.54,0:12:07.94,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He's only fifteen...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.15,0:12:10.63,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,It says here he's still in high school.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:10.63,0:12:12.92,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing scores from all the judges.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:12.92,0:12:14.69,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Eiji Nizuma, huh.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.69,0:12:16.47,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He kind of pisses me off.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:16.47,0:12:17.15,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.15,0:12:19.11,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the 'A Word from the Author' section.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:19.11,0:12:24.05,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,"When everyone was off playing video games, I stayed in and worked hard.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:24.63,0:12:28.80,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll continue to work hard in order to \Nbecome a bestseller in Jack one day."
Dialogue: 5,0:12:28.80,0:12:32.70,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Feels like he's insulting me for being one of those gamers.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.11,0:12:36.25,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,We can surpass guys like this easily, don't worry!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:36.25,0:12:39.54,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,If you look closely, the only thing he's \Ngetting praised for is his planning ability.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:39.54,0:12:41.48,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,That's some confidence you've got there.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:41.48,0:12:44.18,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,The rules are confidence, effort, and luck, aren't they?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:44.18,0:12:46.85,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,That's pride, effort, and luck.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:47.44,0:12:49.33,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Confidence sounds better, don't you think?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.24,0:12:52.16,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Ohh, Kochikame...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.79,0:12:56.04,Q_Q,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Winner of the Tezuka prize at fifteen...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:57.93,0:12:59.09,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Moritaka!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:59.09,0:12:59.80,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:59.80,0:13:02.33,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're excited about getting the studio,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:02.33,0:13:05.41,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,But hanging out there every day is a little too much.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.41,0:13:07.53,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You have exams coming up, you know!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:07.53,0:13:08.43,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.43,0:13:10.14,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.14,0:13:11.50,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then focus on your—
Dialogue: 5,0:13:11.50,0:13:13.69,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Could I have seconds please?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:14.63,0:13:15.31,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.51,0:13:17.62,Default,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Kayoko.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:24.58,0:13:26.08,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going up to the roof.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:27.80,0:13:30.03,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up! I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:31.03,0:13:34.00,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's great! So moe.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:34.00,0:13:36.91,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you're a pro already!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:36.91,0:13:40.79,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess so. If I got serious, I'd take the whole manga industry by storm.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:40.79,0:13:45.31,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, next I'll think up a story, so will you draw the pictures?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:45.31,0:13:48.86,Default,Ishikawa,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I could. But my rates are pretty expensive.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:51.05,0:13:53.40,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.40,0:13:54.39,Default,Ishikawa,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:54.98,0:13:57.39,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Why is everyone looking in the same direction?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.24,0:14:00.61,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,And you didn't draw past their shoulders.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:03.28,0:14:05.45,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys were laughing, weren't they?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:05.45,0:14:07.43,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,That was Takagi from class 2, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:07.43,0:14:08.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Who was the other guy?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:08.70,0:14:11.16,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Who was he again...?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:11.55,0:14:13.30,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.30,0:14:16.58,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Kaya Miyoshi, Azuki's best friend.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:16.58,0:14:17.51,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You know her?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.51,0:14:19.29,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I was asking about the guy who was drawing.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:19.29,0:14:22.54,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Ishizawa. Same grade as us.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.35,0:14:25.47,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Does he wanna be a manga artist?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.47,0:14:30.30,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder. It could just be a cry for attention.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.30,0:14:34.24,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,But if even Miyoshi could tell, his {\i1}in{\i0}ability is sure to be exposed.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:37.70,0:14:41.29,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Don't start slacking off just because midterms are over!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:41.29,0:14:44.46,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Because you still have your high school entrance exams.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.46,0:14:49.43,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Use these exams to think seriously about your futures.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:49.43,0:14:50.95,Default,Students,0000,0000,0000,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:50.95,0:14:53.18,Default,Teacher,0000,0000,0000,,Right, time for class to start then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.24,0:14:57.24,School,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\frx18\fry20\frz348.413\move(-90,139,295,179)}Johoku Prep School
Dialogue: 5,0:14:54.57,0:14:57.25,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, I've got the story just about planned out.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:57.25,0:15:00.18,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get to the studio, I'll start firing off these names like crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.16,0:15:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord1.5\an8\fs25\3c&H000000&\pos(235,22)}{\c&H584FD2&}Summer Course   {\fs20}Now Open\N{\c&HFFFFFF&}This {\c&H584FD2&}summer {\c&HFFFFFF&}is your {\c&H43C4CC&}chance{\c&HFFFFFF&}!\N{\c&H43C4CC&}Build up your foundation{\c&HFFFFFF&} and put \N yourself in the {\c&H584FD2&}lead{\c&HFFFFFF&}!   Johoku Prep School
Dialogue: 5,0:15:01.95,0:15:02.62,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Saiko?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:03.34,0:15:04.17,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:04.46,0:15:08.05,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There are probably a decent number of people \Ntrying to become manga artists like us, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:08.51,0:15:09.56,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Probably, yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:09.56,0:15:11.83,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Nizuma's only fifteen, remember?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:11.83,0:15:15.55,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,There's Ishizawa too. But I don't know how serious he is.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:17.77,0:15:20.23,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided: I'm fine just going to North Yakusa High.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:23.37,0:15:24.86,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,North Yakusa?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:25.32,0:15:29.25,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a safety school for someone like you.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:29.25,0:15:31.71,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But for me, it's the lowest level that my parents still find acceptable.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:31.71,0:15:34.87,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I want as much time as I can get to draw manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:34.87,0:15:37.90,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You're planning everything around becoming a manga artist, huh.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.52,0:15:41.87,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I've never realized time was such a precious resource.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:42.69,0:15:45.33,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been this serious about anything before either!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:45.33,0:15:49.34,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You sure it's okay if you don't go to the same high school as Azuki?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.34,0:15:51.03,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know where she's gonna go.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.64,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,She might end up at an all girl's school.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:52.64,0:15:53.89,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You could just ask her.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:53.89,0:15:56.19,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's fine if we go to different schools.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:56.19,0:15:57.38,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's more...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:57.85,0:15:59.54,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,romantic that way.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:59.54,0:16:00.51,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.51,0:16:03.06,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,The DNA of an idealist...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:06.94,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,0)\fs25\bord0\c&H8A7591&\fnEPSON Pwwww\frx26\fry358\frz343.345\move(647,155,681,154,0,3700)}Graduation\NCeremony
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.05,0:16:06.97,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The next time we meet after middle school,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:07.95,0:16:09.38,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be a manga artist,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:09.38,0:16:11.30,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,And she'll be a voice actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.94,0:16:16.03,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs25\bord0\fnCorporate Rounded\c&H818F9E&\pos(381,231)\frz16.557}Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:16.03,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs15\bord0\fnCorporate Rounded\c&H818F9E&\frz15.772\pos(465,120)}Miho Azuki
Dialogue: 5,0:16:12.54,0:16:15.34,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, you'll just support each other through texts!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:16.50,0:16:17.37,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:17.37,0:16:18.22,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:19.34,0:16:22.66,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really want to copy your uncle that much?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:22.66,0:16:24.25,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,It's what {\i1}I{\i0} wanna do.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:24.25,0:16:26.74,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I think Azuki would like it this way too.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:26.74,0:16:28.07,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Saiko.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:28.07,0:16:32.13,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't even considered the possibility that Azuki will find another guy at her school?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:32.13,0:16:33.90,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:33.90,0:16:35.64,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in Azuki.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.31,0:16:40.43,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,You're really going to North Yakusa, even if it means being separated from Azuki.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.14,0:16:43.45,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Just to get more time to draw manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:43.45,0:16:44.23,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:48.17,0:16:50.40,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Then I guess I'll go there too.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:50.40,0:16:51.26,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:51.26,0:16:53.95,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,You should go to a good college prep school!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:53.95,0:16:55.72,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,If we're aiming to be manga artists together,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.72,0:16:59.90,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Then going to the same school is more convenient.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:59.90,0:17:02.13,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to waste time either.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:02.13,0:17:07.33,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,And also... I'm really grateful for this.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:07.33,0:17:11.05,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I originally thought I'd go to a good college, in case becoming a manga artist didn't work out.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:11.05,0:17:14.16,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,But I realized it's stupid to plan for failure.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:14.16,0:17:15.43,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Shujin...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:16.16,0:17:17.59,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,North Yakusa for me as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:17.59,0:17:19.20,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare fail, Saiko!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:19.20,0:17:22.35,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I won't! I'll concentrate on my \Ndrawing now that I've decided!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:22.71,0:17:26.00,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stand to be beaten by kids our age anymore!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:26.00,0:17:27.18,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.55,0:17:31.04,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Eiji Nizuma is our first rival, huh.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:31.30,0:17:37.82,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Eiji already discussed with his editor: graduating high school and getting serialized simultaneously.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:38.69,0:17:40.70,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,He already has an editor?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:40.90,0:17:42.62,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm positive he does.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:42.62,0:17:45.01,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Once he gets that prize, it's like automatic.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:45.01,0:17:49.38,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,If there's an editor who takes a liking to you, \Nyou can get paired up even without that prize.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:49.38,0:17:50.95,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle said so.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:51.37,0:17:52.94,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,An editor...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:52.94,0:17:56.31,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Eiji's getting farther and farther away from us.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:56.56,0:17:58.78,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The quality and type of editor varies widely.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:58.78,0:18:01.73,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,So getting one at random is not always a great thing either.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:01.73,0:18:06.41,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Since the manga artist can't choose the editor \Nhimself, whether the editor is any good or not...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:06.41,0:18:07.29,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Depends on luck.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:07.82,0:18:10.72,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There are editors whose reputations are totally off.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:10.72,0:18:14.34,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There are editors who just come to pick up your work and do nothing else.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:14.34,0:18:15.86,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There really are all types. You never know.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:15.86,0:18:17.45,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:17.45,0:18:21.21,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Now for a sort of heartwarming editor story:
Dialogue: 5,0:18:21.21,0:18:21.76,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ready!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:23.75,0:18:27.06,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,There was an editor who told a novice manga \Nartist who'd been published elsewhere before,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:27.06,0:18:32.00,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,"I have good feelings about your work. Write more and bring them here!"
Dialogue: 5,0:18:32.45,0:18:36.51,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But after he read about ten of them...
Dialogue: 5,0:18:38.68,0:18:40.51,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,He ran them through the shredder?!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.18,0:18:43.70,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,How is this heartwarming at all?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:43.70,0:18:49.10,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,The novice was used to being turned \Ndown after they read the first couple pages.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:49.10,0:18:52.51,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,So he was really happy someone \Nread his work all the way to the end.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:52.51,0:18:57.62,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,In the pain and frustration of having his work \Nshredded, he joined a group of famous manga artists.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:58.39,0:19:00.74,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a good story now.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.74,0:19:03.30,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,And then, at his serialization meeting,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:03.30,0:19:05.25,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry about doing that back then.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:05.25,0:19:08.65,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought that you might grow, and \Nimprove even more if I {\i1}didn't{\i0} praise you.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:08.65,0:19:11.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:13.45,0:19:15.25,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't sound true.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:16.16,0:19:19.52,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly that editor became editor-in-chief after that.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:19.52,0:19:21.76,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a manga story.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:23.73,0:19:28.64,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle said most editors are like \Nthat, really passionate about manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:28.64,0:19:31.38,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,He said they're all people who just love manga.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:33.16,0:19:33.77,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:34.04,0:19:34.77,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.11,0:19:37.26,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna go see an editor?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:39.20,0:19:43.03,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,If we called and said we had something to show them, we could probably meet one.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:43.03,0:19:46.61,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,We probably could, but we \Ndon't have anything to show yet!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:46.61,0:19:49.27,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's finish something over summer break!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.94,0:19:53.02,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Then bring it to Jack!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:53.50,0:19:57.71,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Jack's the best option since we\Nwant an anime and serialization!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:58.63,0:20:00.59,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,If it doesn't work out, we don't lose anything!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.59,0:20:04.79,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Let's find out what an editor would think of our work.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:05.26,0:20:08.85,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see if our combined talents can get through to them!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:09.90,0:20:11.48,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's do it!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:12.81,0:20:16.73,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Let's finish a work over summer break and bring it to Jack!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.73,0:20:17.45,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:17.98,0:20:20.46,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Now that's out of the way, let's get to work!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:20.46,0:20:21.12,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:25.37,0:20:26.12,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:32.95,0:20:33.80,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Azuki...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:34.50,0:20:39.16,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,I knew she had a younger sister but I didn't know she was this cute.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:39.16,0:20:41.20,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Oh man, what do I do?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:41.20,0:20:42.70,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the time to freeze up!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:42.70,0:20:44.14,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,It's your chance to ask for her email!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:44.97,0:20:47.56,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,But her lioness of a mother is here too.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.56,0:20:49.57,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she'd be dangerous one-on-one.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:49.57,0:20:50.96,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:51.31,0:20:54.09,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just pretend we didn't \Nnotice them and not say anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:54.09,0:20:54.92,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.45,0:20:56.77,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of obvious we {\i1}did{\i0} notice...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:56.77,0:20:57.73,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,Just go!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:00.48,0:21:02.55,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like she's noticed us too.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:03.49,0:21:05.43,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,She's clearly blushing too.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:05.43,0:21:06.82,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,And hiding behind her mom!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:06.84,0:21:08.91,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,No one asked for live commentary!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:20.04,0:21:23.39,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Miho, aren't those your classmates?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:24.01,0:21:26.14,Default,Sister,0000,0000,0000,,Your face is all red, sis!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:26.14,0:21:26.90,Default,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,Mina!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:27.60,0:21:30.54,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you are so shy.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:30.54,0:21:33.65,Default,Takagi,0000,0000,0000,,It's impressive that you can pretend not to \Nknow each other when you're in the same class.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.65,0:21:35.02,Default,Saiko,0000,0000,0000,,I said shut up!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:31.02,0:22:34.54,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The editor-in-chief praised your work as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.41,0:22:34.53,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\fs25\bord1.5\be1\fnEPSON Pwwww\pos(191,332)\c&H0E1620&\3c&H3C7CB7&}Nizuma
Dialogue: 5,0:22:34.54,0:22:37.50,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I also have confidence in your skills.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:38.50,0:22:41.66,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I think it'd be a great idea for you to come to Tokyo...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:43.11,0:22:44.43,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Nizuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.48,0:22:49.82,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,The boring everyday gets to me sometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.48,0:22:49.82,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Betaa na Genjitsu ni Tsubusaretemo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.82,0:22:55.99,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,but I always get back on my feet, standing strong
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.82,0:22:55.99,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Uchinomesareta Jibun Hiroiatsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.99,0:23:00.74,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times the end approaches me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.99,0:23:00.74,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Nando Owari ga Otozuretemo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.74,0:23:07.08,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll push my own back forward, keeping me on my feet
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.74,0:23:07.08,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonotabi ni Jibun de Jibun no Senaka Oshita
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.08,0:23:12.01,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,If I get lost in the meaning of continuing what I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.08,0:23:12.01,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuzuiteku Imi ni Nayami
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.01,0:23:16.89,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll rid myself of those worries and keep myself going forward
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.01,0:23:16.89,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Sono Mayoi Sae Tachikitte Yuku
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.89,0:23:18.05,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,Always
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.89,0:23:18.05,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Itsumo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.05,0:23:23.18,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,The straight edge that draws the outline of my future
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.05,0:23:23.18,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Mirai no Rinkakusen Kaku Massugu na Jougi wa
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.18,0:23:28.86,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,is made of all the courage I've mustered up until today
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.18,0:23:28.86,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Ikutsumo no Kinou no Yuuki de Dekiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.86,0:23:33.94,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll climb over the tall wall that I never thought I'd face,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.86,0:23:33.94,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Omoiegaita no to Chigau Takai Kabe Koe
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:39.99,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,and continue my journey, going past the vanishing point
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:39.99,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoushisuten no Mukou e Susunde
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.24,0:23:46.17,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,This winding road seems to never end,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.24,0:23:46.17,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Harukanaru Winding Road
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.17,0:23:52.17,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,but it is the road I personally chose
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.17,0:23:52.17,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Hoka no Dare Demo Nai Watashi ga Jibun de Eranda
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.17,0:23:59.76,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,I set my tiny dreams on fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.17,0:23:59.76,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Kasuka na Yume o Zenbu Moyashita
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.76,0:24:03.97,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,and broke through the dark with its light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.76,0:24:03.97,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Sono Hikari de Yami o Saite
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.97,0:24:08.02,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've broken down the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.97,0:24:08.02,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudaita Kabe no Mukou ni
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.02,0:24:13.48,Songs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1500)}I can see my sky once more
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.02,0:24:13.48,Songs - R,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1500)}Jibun no Sora ga Mieru
Dialogue: 5,0:24:15.43,0:24:17.95,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Miho, don't you think Takagi likes you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.45,0:24:19.76,Next Ep,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(75,47)\clip(0,48,852,147)}Next\NEpisode
Dialogue: 5,0:24:17.95,0:24:20.14,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he asked me about your secret dream before, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:20.14,0:24:20.83,Default,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,That was just...
Dialogue: 5,0:24:20.83,0:24:21.76,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,What, what?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:21.76,0:24:22.81,Default,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll tell you someday.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:22.81,0:24:23.44,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.43,0:24:29.65,Next Ep,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(75,47)\clip(0,48,852,146)}Summer\Nand Names
Dialogue: 5,0:24:23.73,0:24:25.56,Default,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Summer and Names.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:25.56,0:24:27.84,Default,Azuki,0000,0000,0000,,Summer is a busy time for those chasing their dreams!
